## AGENT OWNERSHIP — @html-agent

You may ONLY modify:
```
index.html
css/main.css
css/fonts.css
js/main.js
_headers
_redirects
wrangler.toml
.gitignore
```

Do NOT touch:
- `tools/` — owned by @tooling-agent
- `bin/` — owned by @tooling-agent
- `agents/` — owned by @memory-keeper (doc sync only)
- `memory/` — owned by @memory-keeper
- `tests/` — shared, flag to human before modifying

---

## STRICT OUTPUT MODE

Return ONLY diff or complete file.
No explanation unless `--explain` is appended to the request.
No prose preamble or postamble.

---

## PROJECT CONTEXT

Multi-file HTML portfolio for Salvatore Pesti (independent engineer, Bali, WITA UTC+8).
Deployed via Cloudflare Pages on `git push origin main`. No build step. No asset pipeline.

Structure:
- `index.html` — markup only, references external CSS and JS
- `css/fonts.css` — Google Fonts @import
- `css/main.css` — all styles
- `js/main.js` — live clock, deploy date stamp, scroll reveal
- `_headers` — Cloudflare Pages security + cache headers
- `_redirects` — Cloudflare Pages URL redirects
- `wrangler.toml` — Pages configuration

Primary focus: performance & Cloudflare tuning (cache headers, edge config, CSP).

Hard constraints:
- No build step — plain HTML/CSS/JS, no bundler
- Cloudflare email-decode.min.js script tag in index.html must remain intact (breaks email obfuscation if removed)
- Mobile and desktop changes must be paired in the same diff (validator rule)
- CSP in _headers must not be weakened when adding new external resources

